node.text: White Cube LIRCAEI, designed by OMA / David Gianotten and located in the Democratic Republic of Congo, is featured in White Cube, a documentary by Renzo Martens in collaboration with CATPC. The film will premiere at IDFA and in Lusanga on 21 November, before touring globally. White Cube LIRCAEI—a museum for display and sales of art created by the African community—is part of the OMA-designed LIRCAEI masterplan supporting a new art economic model, which includes the often exploited Congolese labourers in art’s creation and profit sharing. #lusanga #davidgianotten #IDFA @catpc_lusanga #CATPC #renzomartens #whitecube, #whitecubefilm

node.text: #OMAresearch Europe is known as the old continent. Current demographic trends may soon declare it the elderly continent. In a society where the elderly are likely to become the many, and caregivers become ever fewer, how are we going to take care of the next generations when they grow old or fall ill? #oma #research #reinierdegraaf #hopitaldufutur

node.text:
Brighton College, School of Science and Sport, designed by OMA / Ellen van Loon, has won a @RIBA award for the South East region. Observing that processes of learning take place outside as much as inside of the classroom, the design articulates a new idea of educational space bolstering interaction and exchange.

Photography by @laurianghinitoiu and @kilianosullivan #ellenvanloon #oma #brighton #brightoncollege

node.text: Taipei Performing Arts Center designed by OMA’s David Gianotten and Rem Koolhaas is featured in TIME’s list of the World’s Greatest Places 2021. Located at Taipei’s Shilin Night Market, the building consists of three theaters plugged into a central cube, allowing performing spaces to be coupled for new theatrical possibilities. A Public Loop extends street life of Taipei into the theater. Photography by @shephotoerd @time @taipeiperformingartscenter #davidgianotten #remkoolhaas #taipei

node.text:
The AMO designed Off-White Paris Flagship store combines Parisian elegance with industrial rawness, rethinking Parisian high-end retail. A courtyard, a gallery and a market extend over three floors, gradually revealing to the visitor Off White’s diverse identity. The contrasting combinations of textures and colors emphasize the store's repertoire of ambiences, creating an abstract reinterpretation of Paris. 

Images by @benoitflorencon. #ellenvanloon @samirbantal @giuliomargheri @off___white__paris @virgilabloh

node.text:
The Qianhai International Financial Exchange Center (IFEC) is a mixed use complex, designed as a connector between Qianhai—a new district in Shenzhen—and the waterfront. 

The three volumes include a stepping-shaped conference center with terraces facing the bay and the park, a tilted block for hotel amenities and public programs oriented towards the central axis of the business district, and a polyhedron-shaped hotel that sits on top, with views open to all directions. The volumes form an urban atrium that opens up a public route between Qianhai’s future main transportation hub and the waterfront park. The atrium can also function as a place for cultural events and daily leisure activities.

#qianhai #chrisvanduijn
